  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Mobile networks are defaulted to `Enabled` to Status app . User can revoke the permissions manually and forget about it, like if he runs status under wifi mostly and dont want to occasionally waste mobile trafic (could be expensive). \r\n\r\nOnce switched to 3G after some time this user won' receive messages or send them, and will be shown offline when using Status because Status is not allowed to use mobile data and user does not know about it (there is no any tooltip or hint saying that app is about to use mobile data , please grant the permissions)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWhen i switch off mobile data permissions for Status in the device settings and then run status under mobile network i want to see notification asking for permissions to enable mobile data usage (same as we do for camera permissions or google maps do when you are trying to get directions with geolocation disabled)\r\n\r\nWe can show similar notifcation as below with the following text:\r\n\r\n`Status Would Like to Access Mobile Data` or similar. When user taps `OK` he is redirected to settings page for particular Status app where he can enable mobile data. If user taps `Don't allow` - the message is closed and mobile data permissions are not granted to Status app.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/39756481-82efec5a-52d2-11e8-8602-a0fb2cef7fd2.png)\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/39756538-b5f00464-52d2-11e8-94ad-a593a4a9592c.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n`Error connecting to mailserver` along with `offline` tooltip that confuses user.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Check that mobile data usage is not allowed for Status app in device settings\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Use mobile 3G internet\r\n- Start messaging\r\n- Pay attention to the banner\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: last nightly\r\n* Operating System: iOS 11.3.1, iPhone 7\r\n",
